---
import ProseLayout from '../../layouts/ProseLayout.astro';
import ControllerIdentity from '../../components/privacy/ControllerIdentity.astro';
import ChildrensPrivacy from '../../components/privacy/ChildrensPrivacy.astro';
import PrivacyContact from '../../components/privacy/PrivacyContact.astro';
---

<ProseLayout
  title="dayGLANCE Privacy Policy"
  description="How dayGLANCE handles your data. Short version: we don't collect it, and anything you sync goes to a destination you control."
  lastUpdated="July 10, 2026"
>
  <p class="lead">
    Short version: dayGLANCE does not collect, store, or share your personal
    data. Your information stays on your device unless you choose to sync it to
    a destination you control.
  </p>

  <ControllerIdentity>
    <p>
      This policy covers dayGLANCE specifically. For our publisher-level
      practices and the glance-apps.com website, see the{' '}
      <a href="/privacy">GLANCE Apps privacy policy</a>.
    </p>
  </ControllerIdentity>

  <h2>Data stored on your device</h2>
  <p>
    All content you create in dayGLANCE, such as your tasks, notes, intentions,
    habits, and reflections, is stored locally on your device using your
    platform's standard on-device storage. This data remains under your control
    at all times.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you use your platform's automatic backup service (iCloud Backup, Google
    Backup, or similar), your device data may be backed up as part of your
    standard device backup. This is governed by your platform provider's privacy
    policy.
  </p>

  <h2>Cloud sync and backup</h2>
  <p>
    dayGLANCE supports optional cloud sync and remote backup to destinations you
    configure. Two kinds of destination are supported, and they use different
    encryption models.
  </p>
  <p>
    WebDAV-compatible servers (such as Nextcloud) and GLANCEvault: files are
    encrypted client-side before leaving your device using AES-256-GCM, with
    keys derived from a sync passphrase you choose via PBKDF2. The server stores
    only opaque ciphertext and never has access to your plaintext data, your
    passphrase, or your encryption key. This is a zero-knowledge architecture.
    GLANCEvault is a sync server you run on your own infrastructure; GLANCE Apps
    does not operate any GLANCEvault instance and has no access to its contents.
  </p>
  <p>
    iCloud Drive: if you choose iCloud Drive, your files are stored in your
    personal iCloud account and protected by Apple's standard encryption. This
    path does not use the app's passphrase-derived encryption described above.
    Apple's privacy policy governs data stored in iCloud.
  </p>
  <p>
    Your passphrase is never stored anywhere. So that you are not prompted on
    every launch, the derived key is cached locally on your device: on Android
    it is held in the hardware-backed Android Keystore, and on iOS, macOS, and
    the web app it is stored in the app's sandboxed local storage. If you forget
    your passphrase, your encrypted data cannot be recovered. This is by design.
  </p>

  <h2>Health Data (Health Connect and HealthKit)</h2>
  <p>
    dayGLANCE offers optional health integration. If you enable it, dayGLANCE
    reads your step count and sleep data from Health Connect on Android or
    HealthKit on iOS, solely to display and reflect on that information within
    the app. This data is used on your device and is never written back to
    Health Connect or HealthKit, and it is never transmitted to any server we
    control. Health integration is off by default.
  </p>

  <h2>AI features</h2>
  <p>
    dayGLANCE offers optional AI features that require you to configure access to
    an AI provider of your choice (such as Ollama for local processing, or a
    cloud provider like OpenAI or Anthropic). AI features are off by default.
    When you use them, the data you choose to send is transmitted to the provider
    you selected and is governed by that provider's terms and privacy policy.
    GLANCE Apps does not operate AI services and does not have access to data you
    send to AI providers.
  </p>

  <h2>Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    dayGLANCE does not use third-party analytics services. Your platform's
    distribution service (such as Apple's App Store Connect or Google Play
    Console) may share aggregated, anonymized crash and usage data with us if you
    have opted into analytics on your device. This data cannot be used to
    identify you individually.
  </p>

  <h2>Payments and subscriptions</h2>
  <p>
    dayGLANCE may offer in-app purchases and subscriptions. On Android these are
    processed entirely by Google Play; on iOS and macOS they are processed
    entirely by the Apple App Store. We do not collect, see, or store your
    payment information. The relevant store may share a purchase token with the
    app solely to verify your subscription status; this token is used on your
    device and is not transmitted to dayGLANCE servers (there are none). The
    applicable store's privacy policy governs all payment processing.
  </p>
  <p>
    To manage subscription entitlements across platforms, dayGLANCE uses
    RevenueCat. RevenueCat receives an anonymized app-user identifier and
    purchase and subscription events (such as which product was purchased and
    whether a subscription is active) in order to determine your entitlement
    status. RevenueCat does not receive your name, your app content, or other
    personally identifying information. RevenueCat's privacy policy governs its
    handling of this data.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-party services</h2>
  <p>
    dayGLANCE can interoperate with third-party services at your direction. When
    you enable a feature that uses one, your use of that service is governed by
    its own terms and privacy policy. These may include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>A CalDAV or Nextcloud server (calendar sync)</li>
    <li>A WebDAV or Nextcloud server (file sync)</li>
    <li>A GLANCEvault instance you self-host</li>
    <li>iCloud Drive (protected by Apple's standard encryption)</li>
    <li>Your AI provider</li>
    <li>The Apple App Store or Google Play (purchase verification)</li>
    <li>RevenueCat (entitlement management)</li>
  </ul>

  <ChildrensPrivacy />

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    If we make material changes to this policy, we will update the "Last updated"
    date at the top of this page and notify users through the app or this website
    before changes take effect.
  </p>

  <PrivacyContact />
</ProseLayout>
